">Launched in 1983, it was more than a car &#8211; it made cars accessible to middle-class Indians and captured our imagination for over two decades.&#xA0;<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The 800cc vehicle sold by Suzuki until March 31st, 2015 clocked up 1.8 million bookings since its launch 30 years ago.&#xA0;<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It revolutionized people&#8217;s mobility on Indian roads with its low price tag and fuel efficiency at a time when imported cars were expensive and sparsely available to average consumers.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Which_is_the_most_sold_car_in_India_of_all_time\"><\/span>Which is the most sold car in India of all time?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maruti Suzuki Alto, which is a supermini car has sold more than 1 million cars to date.&#xA0;<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was launched on 19 April 1983.&#xA0;<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The name &#x2018;Alto&#x2019; is derived from the Italian word meaning high and above.&#xA0;<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The car was first unveiled as Maruti 800 at Delhi Auto Expo 2014, but later it was renamed Alto 800 because of a trademark infringement suit filed by Mahindra &amp; Mahindra.&#xA0;<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was marketed under a different name only for two months prior to its actual launch in India as it generated huge demand due to its affordable price tag.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Which_is_the_most_famous_car_in_India\"><\/span><b>Which is the most famous car in India?&#xA0;<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Maruti Suzuki 800 is a car produced by Suzuki Motor Corporation in collaboration with Maruti Udyog, now known as Maruti Suzuki India Limited.&#xA0;<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was launched on 8 January 1983. With 434,051 units sold, it was one of the most successful cars in the history of the Indian automobile industry.&#xA0;<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Even today after over 25 years of production and sales, it is remembered for its unique design and low-cost maintenance.&#xA0;<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The second best-selling car is the Hindustan Ambassador which with more than 632000+ units sold from 1958 to 2012 at the time of writing makes it India&#8217;s longest-running production car by any brand to date.&#xA0;<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A classic retro vehicle that helped Hindustan Motors gain market share before competition from other foreign brands forced them out of business.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Best-selling_cars_in_India_in_2022\"><\/span><b>Best-selling cars in India in 2022<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maruti Suzuki Alto 800, Maruti Suzuki Swift, Maruti Suzuki Alto K10, Maruti Suzuki Wagon R, Mahindra Scorpio, Mahindra Bolero. Mahindra Xylo, Honda City and Skoda Yeti. In terms of numbers sold more than 3 million units each with three cars crossing 2 million mark sales; however, their percentage will be less as compared to others.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Conclusion\"><\/span><b>Conclusion<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\